437
00:24:24,420 --> 00:24:25,260
Miss Cui,

438
00:24:25,980 --> 00:24:26,980
let's go listen to some music first

439
00:24:27,260 --> 00:24:28,660
before taking a boat tour.

440
00:24:37,740 --> 00:24:38,260
This is

441
00:24:38,340 --> 00:24:39,300
where we are right now.

442
00:24:39,380 --> 00:24:40,620
If anything happens,

443
00:24:40,700 --> 00:24:42,540
we can take the route in the north.

444
00:24:43,180 --> 00:24:43,860
Keep that in mind.

445
00:24:45,940 --> 00:24:46,780
And here…

446
00:24:48,820 --> 00:24:49,540
Hey, monk.

447
00:24:49,980 --> 00:24:51,380
What are you thinking about?

448
00:24:55,700 --> 00:24:57,020
Actually, I'm a little afraid.

449
00:24:57,500 --> 00:24:58,460
Of what?

450
00:25:00,420 --> 00:25:02,220
I'm afraid that the emperor of Nanxiao would break his promise.

451
00:25:02,300 --> 00:25:04,100
After all, holding the junior Prince of Nanchen hostage,

452
00:25:04,100 --> 00:25:04,860
it's no different

453
00:25:04,860 --> 00:25:05,820
from controlling half of our country.

454
00:25:06,260 --> 00:25:07,250
He wouldn't.

455
00:25:09,370 --> 00:25:09,940
Why?

456
00:25:12,420 --> 00:25:13,500
He can be cold-blooded

457
00:25:13,580 --> 00:25:14,940
and skeptical of the people around him,

458
00:25:15,500 --> 00:25:16,100
but he's an emperor

459
00:25:16,220 --> 00:25:17,820
who cares about his people.

460
00:25:18,340 --> 00:25:19,620
He wouldn't want his people

461
00:25:19,700 --> 00:25:20,900
to suffer in a war.

462
00:25:21,660 --> 00:25:23,420
It's easy to detain Zhousheng Chen,

463
00:25:23,660 --> 00:25:25,700
but he can't afford to provoke

464
00:25:26,300 --> 00:25:27,220
his army of 700,000 soldiers.

465
00:25:27,980 --> 00:25:29,220
That's why he wouldn't do that.

466
00:25:33,340 --> 00:25:34,580
You want to say

467
00:25:35,460 --> 00:25:36,380
I know him well, don't you?

468
00:25:39,900 --> 00:25:40,860
I don't dare to.

469
00:25:41,340 --> 00:25:42,380
I don't want to upset you.

470
00:25:44,140 --> 00:25:44,700
In fact, I've thought of a lot

471
00:25:44,820 --> 00:25:46,180
comforting words.

472
00:25:46,580 --> 00:25:48,300
But nothing seems useful.

473
00:25:51,020 --> 00:25:52,620
How about I tell you something about my father?

474
00:25:56,860 --> 00:25:57,980
My father

475
00:25:59,680 --> 00:26:00,630
is actually not much better

476
00:26:00,650 --> 00:26:02,180
compared to your father.

477
00:26:03,460 --> 00:26:04,500
He took away

478
00:26:04,820 --> 00:26:06,140
all my mother's money for medicine

479
00:26:06,260 --> 00:26:07,340
and went to gamble.

480
00:26:07,620 --> 00:26:09,260
None of our relatives offered help.

481
00:26:09,620 --> 00:26:11,940
So in the end, I watched my mother die of illness

482
00:26:13,620 --> 00:26:14,940
right in front of me.

483
00:26:23,580 --> 00:26:24,540
Then one day,

484
00:26:25,500 --> 00:26:26,340
I hid a wine jar

485
00:26:26,460 --> 00:26:28,020
on the door.

486
00:26:28,380 --> 00:26:29,740
When my father came home,

487
00:26:29,860 --> 00:26:31,260
the jar fell and he was almost killed by it.

488
00:26:35,140 --> 00:26:36,380
I was so afraid.

489
00:26:37,860 --> 00:26:39,700
